readme: ## math-clamp-x Clamp a number to limits. ### `module.exports(value, [min], max)` number This method clamp a number to min and max limits inclusive. **Kind**: Exported function **Returns**: number - The clamped number. **Throws**: - RangeError If min > max. | Param | Type | Default | Description | | ----- | ------------------- | -------------- | ------------------------- | | value | number | | The number to be clamped. | | [min] | number | 0 | The minimum number. | | max | number | | The maximum number. | **Example** ```js import mathClamp from 'math-clamp-x'; console.log(mathClamp(-5, 3, 3)); // 3 console.log(mathClamp(0, 3, 3)); // 3 console.log(mathClamp(5, 3, 3)); // 3 ```
